						<div class="postbody">Can we all agree that the best values to have in palette memory when a ROM is loaded is either $0D, $0E or $0F? That way the screen won't flash grey for the first frame or two. I know that all NES's had pre-set values and some say that different colours would flash up, so I think that for neutrality reasons and for best results having a totally black palette on ROM load would be best. I don't believe that any game relies on the palette entries to run, but does anyone else?</div>

					
